OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1774947927
OL,3,CAssembly must take action to protect
OL,4,Ccommunity sector, union warns
OL,6,FThe statement added: "The Northern
OL,7,FIreland Assembly must act now to
OL,8,Fprovide sustainable, long-term funding
OL,9,Fthat protects jobs and ensures the
OL,10,Fcontinuation of essential services.
OL,12,F"At the same time, the Secretary of
OL,13,FState (Hilary Benn) must fulfil his
OL,14,Fobligations to appropriately secure
OL,15,Fand allocate the funding necessary to
OL,16,Fsustain the community and voluntary
OL,17,Fsector in Northern Ireland.
OL,26,@nD@VOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1774947927
OL,3,CAssembly must take action to protect
OL,4,Ccommunity sector, union warns
OL,6,F"Failure to act at both levels will
OL,7,Fnot only result in widespread job
OL,8,Flosses but will also place
OL,9,Funacceptable pressure on already
OL,10,Foverstretched public services.
OL,12,F"Investing in the community and
OL,13,Fvoluntary sector is not optional ` it
OL,14,Fis essential.
OL,16,F"We urge elected representatives and
OL,17,Fthe Secretary of State to recognise
OL,18,Fthe urgency of this crisis and to work
OL,19,Fcollectively to deliver the funding
OL,20,Fsolutions that are so desperately
OL,21,Fneeded."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUxD@AOU}D@HO]
